<Html><Head><Title>CAROL COLLECTION BRINGS CHRISTMAS CHEER FOR PEOPLE WITH AUTISM</title></head>

<Body  bgcolor="#CCFFCC" link="#336633" vlink="#669966">

<i>The material that follows has been provided by <b><a href="../index.html">The National Autistic
Society</a></b></i>

[nas logo]
<hr>
<b>NEWS RELEASE<br>
Date: 5 November 1996 Ref:   NAS/18/96</b>


<h2>CAROL COLLECTION BRINGS CHRISTMAS CHEER FOR PEOPLE WITH AUTISM</h2>

<b>AUTISM AWARENESS WEEK - 2-8 DECEMBER 1996</b><p>

Whatever your favourite Christmas Carol - you'll be sure to find it on the heavenly CD  - 'The Carol
Collection'  from Carlton Classics. The CD features 14 wonderful carols and makes the perfect Christmas
gift for anyone who enjoys traditional music at its best.  What's more,  for every copy sold,  it will also
bring good cheer to The National Autistic Society (NAS) who will benefit by receiving 10% of the sale price
for every one sold.  Priced at £4.99 for the CD and a mere £2.99 for the cassette,  you can afford to buy
more than one!
<p>

The 'Carol Collection' is performed by several choirs including the famous Royal Choral Society, The
Westminster Cathedral Choir and St Paul's Cathedral Choir.  Classics featured on this delightful classic
compilation include Once in Royal David's City', 'In Dulci Jubilo' 'The First Nowell', 'Silent Night',  'O Little Town
of Bethlehem' and 'O Come All Ye Faithful'
<p>

The 'Carol Collection' will really raise the Christmas spirit in your household this season. 
Jane Asher, Vice President of the NAS said:
<blockquote>'The sound of Christmas carols is one of the most stirring and beautiful in the world.  This
compilation contains all my favourites, wonderfully sung and orchestrated, and I know it will delight you as
much as it does me.  At this special time of the year, I'm sure you will also be as pleased as I am that your
purchase will directly benefit a person with the distressing condition of autism' .</blockquote>
<p>

The 'Carol Collection' (catalogue no. 30367 00022) is available from all good record stores.
<hr>
<address>
For further information or a review copy, please contact:  Angela O'Brien, Press & PR Officer or Ann
Stirling, Communications Manager on 0181 451 1114.  Direct Line: 0181 830 4187.
</address>
<Hr>

<Address>The National Autistic Society, 276 Willesden Lane, London NW2 5RB <br>
Tel: 0181 451 1114<br>
Email: <b><A href="mailto:nas@clus1.ulcc.ac.uk"> 

nas@clus1.ulcc.ac.uk</a></b></adDRESS><p>

