<hr width=40%>

<h2>Health and Disease</h2>

<ul type=square>




<li><b><a href="../scf/health/prhealth.html">800 million without health care in poorest countries:</a></b><br>
This year the <b>Save the Children Fund</b> is targeting the health needs of children around the world.  This report - 'Poor in Health' - reveals that 8000 children die every day from dehydration brought about by diarrhoea, while TB kills a further 7000 people every day.<p>

<a name="aids">

<li><b><a href="../unicef/Feb9_press.html">African footballers to lead HIV/AIDS awareness campaign:</a></b><br>
Africa's leading footballers have teamed up with UNICEF to help promote its AIDS prevention and care campaign across the continent.<p>

<li><b><a href="../panos/dec_aids.html">Dual AIDS theory explains Third World epidemic:</a></b><br>
A new theory sees two distinct AIDS epidemics, with different strains of the deadly disease affecting the industrialised world and the developing world, reports </b>PANOS</b>.<p>


<b><font size=+1>World Aids Day - 1 December
</font></b><p>

<li><b><a href="../panos/india.html">India's race against time:</a></b><br>
There is a huge danger facing countries which respond too slowly to the AIDS threat, stresses
       Daleep Mukarji, former head of the Christian Medical Association of India (CMA).<p>

<br><b><a href="wad_special.html">More features on <br>World AIDS Day </a></b><br clear=all><p>
