<head>
<title>Refugee Council criticises asylum proposals</title> 
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#823308" alink="d9d919" vlink="ff7f00">OneWorld News Service

<p><b><font size=-1>This material has been provided by The Refugee Council</font></b>
<center><h2>No need for new legislation, says Refugee Council
</h2></center>
<p>
        
 
<b>15 November 1995</b><p>
 
 In response to the announcement of a new Asylum and Immigration Bill in the Queen's speech, Nick Hardwick, Chief Executive of the Refugee Council says:<p>

"We profoundly regret that such a controversial issue is being considered in the run up to an election and we hope that politicians of all parties would not seek to make capital out of the unfounded fears and prejudice that surrounds this issue.<p>

"It would be a tragedy if matters of life and death for individual asylum seekers are decided with one eye on the forthcoming general election.<p>

"There is no need for new legislation, instead resources should be directed to ensuring the existing procedures are fair and just."<p>
<hr>
<i>For further information, please contact Sue Simmonds on + 44 (0)171 820 3044.</i><p>




