<br><HR><BR>
<H1><CENTER>Teachers' Notes - Further activities using the photographs <BR>
and stories </CENTER>
</H1>
<HR>


<h2 ALIGN=CENTER>COCONUT BISCUITS</h2>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD>
175g plain flour<BR>
1 teaspoon baking powder<BR>
75g castor sugar<BR>
1 tablespoon milk<BR>
375g flaked coconut<BR>
3 tablespoons butter<BR>
1 egg<br></TD>
<td></td>
<tr><td><br>1. Mix the flour and the baking powder in a bowl</td><td><br>2. Make a well in the flour and pour the butter in the centre.</td>
<tr><td><br>3. Add half the flaked coconut with the sugar.</td><td><br>4. Mix quickly with your fingers.</td>
<tr><td><br>5. Whisk the egg and add it with the milk to the mixture.</td><td><br>6. Mix with your hands to make a dough.</td>
<tr><td><br>7. Lightly grease your hands.</td><td><br>8. Roll the dough into 20 small pieces.</td>
<tr><td><br>9. Roll the balls of dough in the remaining coconut flakes.</td><td><br>10. Grease a baking tray and arrange the balls on it.</td>
<tr><td><br>11. Bake for 15 minutes in the oven (180c)</td><td></td>
</TR>
</TABLE>




