<h1>People and their environment</h1>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<ul type=square>
<li><b><a href="../cafod/famine.htm">CAFOD Factsheet: Famine</a></b><br>
What are the causes of famine and where are the high risk zones?<br>
<li><b><a href="../patp/pap_victoria.html">People and the Planet: Lake Victoria - a Dying Sea</a></b><br>
The lake is in poor health and threatening the livlihood of the communities around it. Nancy Chege, of the Worldwatch Institute, reports.<br>
<li><b><a href="../patp/people_aralsea.html">People and the Planet: Aral Sea - a Health Disaster Revealed</a></b><br>
One million people in the former Soviet Republic of Karakalpakia are under immediate health threats from toxic pollution ...<br>
<b><li type=square><a href="../patp/pap_consump.html">People and the Planet: Towards a New Culture of Consumption</a></b><br>
A radical change is needed in the way we think about raw materials used to fuel our consumer society, John Young gives you the facts.</ul>
<br><br></BLOCKQUOTE>

<a name="freedom">

<center>[break][break][break]</center><br>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<h1>Freedom of expression</h1>
<blockquote>
<ul type=square>
<li><b><a href="../cba/sept96/china.htm">CBA: Growing Concern About Freedom of Expression in Hong Kong after 1997:</a></b><br>
China has begun to impose its own limits on press freedom in Hong Kong. Editors have been urged to tone down stories that were not to China's liking, and there has been a significant increase in the number of journalists detained or harassed. The Hong Kong Journalists Association is still hoping that Beijing will respect the rights and freedom that Hong Kong's people currently enjoy.<br>
<li><b><a href="../news/partner_news/may96_hrw.html">Human Rights Watch: Worldwide Efforts to Censor Internet Expand:</a></b><br>
Freedom of expression on the Internet is in serious danger across the globe.  Governments across the globe are rushing to impose controls, using excuses such as protecting children and thwarting terrorists to justify their actions.<br>
<li><b><a href="../news/partner_news/hrw/index.html">Human Rights Watch: Silencing the Net - The Threat to Freedom of Expression Online</a></b><br>
The full Human Rights Watch report - giving a worldwide breakdown of how freedom in cyberspace is threatened in different countries.  Censorship legislation is being enacted or considered by governments of all political colours - led, ironically, by the United States, birthplace of the Internet.<br>
<li><b><a href="../index_oc/9602/saudi.html">Index on Censorship: Censorship and Control in the International Arab Press:</a></b><br>
The Kingdom of Saudi Arabia - a country not reknowned for its political openness - owns 95% of the Arabic-lanugage media in Arab countries and abroad.  <br>
<li><b><a href="../index_oc/letter_mar15.html">Index on Censorship: Letter from Lagos - Unleashing the Furies:</a></b><br>
A performance of a play by the Nobel laureate Wole Soyinka gave the Nigerian authorities cause for concern recently, despite the fact that the same play is used in schoolbooks across the country.<br>
<li><b><a href="../index_oc/letter.html">Index on Censorship: Letter from Lagos</b></a><br>
Index on Censorship's correspondent in Nigeria reports on the military dictatorship's abuse of the press, legal system and human rights in the country.  This report is <b>exclusive to Index's Web site</b>.<br>
<li><b><a href="../amnesty/ai_turkey_oct30.html">Amnesty International: Legal Changes Leave Repressive Measures Intact</a> </b><br>
Minor changes to Turkey's Anti-Terror law will still lead to people being jailed for expressing non-violent opinions.<br>
<li><b><a href="../index_oc/news/albania6feb.html">Index on Censorship: Opposition Press and Politicians Under Fire in Albania</b></a><br>
Albania's democratically-elected government has come under attack for passing repressive legislation to silence its critics.<br>
<li><b><a href="http://www.oneworld.org/index_oc/index_movs/wei.ram">Endangered Writers - the Story of Wei Jingsheng</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../index_oc/marlowe.html">Index on Censorship: Journalists Targeted in Civil War</a></b><br>
The ever-mounting cost of Algeria's bitter civil war have hit journalists particularly.  Thirty five have been assassinated by Islamic radicals in the last two years.
As part of <b>Index on Censorship's</b> 'Endangered Writers' series, Frank Ortega tells the story of one Chinese journalist who suffered for his outspokenness. <br>
<li><b><a href="../index_oc/news/cuba5feb.html">Index on Censorship: Cuba Cracks Down on Independent Journalists</a></b><br>
Cuban police are stepping up their campaign of harassment against the country's few independent journalists.<br>
<li><b><a href="../amnesty/ai_azerbaijan.html">Amnesty International: Four Journalists Imprisoned for 'Insulting the President'</a></b><br> Four journalists who caricatured President Heydar Aliyev are now 'prisoners of conscience'.<p>







</ul>
<br><br></BLOCKQUOTE>
</ul>

