<head>
<title>TVE - Developing Stories</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#333366" vlink="#666699">
<font size=5 face=helvetica, arial>
<div align=right><a href="index.html" target="_parent">About TVE</a></div></font>
<h2>Developing Stories</h2>
<font size=2 face=helvetica,arial>In 1989, TVE, in alliance with the BBC and the One World Group of
Broadcasters, pioneered the first Developing Stories series, which provided six outstanding film-makers
from the South with an opportunity to make their own programmes, in their own chosen genres,
presenting their view on environment and development issues. Broadcast in 98 countries in the run-up to
the1992 UN Earth Summit, the six films in this first series went on to win 25 international awards, and to
be used in countless festivals, seminars and educational campaigns. </font>

<p>
<font size=2 face=helvetica,arial>A second series, Developing Stories II, showcased four more films timed
to coincide with the Cairo International Conference on Population and Development in September 1994.
With their focus on the linked issues of population, resource depletion, poverty and migration, issues that
were at the heart of the conference, the series has so far been broadcast in 40 countries. The concept
behind Developing Stories has been adopted for a new series of programmes that has been developed by
TVE to raise awareness of, and coincide with, the Fourth World Conference on Women. Entitled Women of
the World the package of programmes consists of documentaries and shorts, news features and 'spots'
made by Southern women producers, exploring some of the issues on the agenda at the Fourth World
Conference on Women, taking place in Beijing in September 1995.</font>
<pre>
</pre>
