<html>
<head>
<title>A Message of Support from Carol Bellamy</title>
</head>
<body  bgcolor="ffffff" link="238e23" vlink="8fbc8f" alink"cd7f32>


<a href="../index.html" target="_parent">To UNICEF Home Page</a>International Children's Day of Broadcasting Page</a></center>
<br clear=all><br>

<center><br clear=left>

<h2>A Message from Carol Bellamy, <br>UNICEF Executive Director</h2>
</center><p>
<b>
As the new Executive Director of UNICEF, I want to express my support for the International Children's Day of Broadcasting and to urge all of you to be a part of it.  The Day has truly created an 'electronic ring around the world.'<p></b>

During my days at the Peace Corps in Latin America, I saw - and used - the power of radio to communicate vital information.  Television enhances that power.  In just three short years, this Day has shown conclusively that when this power is used for children, their lives change for the better.<p>

For us at UNICEF, this year's International Children's Day of Broadcasting is a very special one, as it kicks off a year of celebrations for the organisation's 50th Anniversary.  We're asking you not only to look back with us, but to look forward at what tomorrow has in store for children.<p>

I believe the Convention on the Rights of the Child holds great hope for the future of our children.  It has been ratified by almost every country in the world.  But without broadcasters to spread the word about its provisions, monitor its implementation and, above all, to give children a voice, the Convention cannot become a living document.  On this year's Day, we're asking you to focus on the Convention and so make children's rights a reality.<p>

Through the International Children's Day of Broadcasting, we hope you will join us on that journey towards tomorrow, to a world where all children can have the chance to grow, develop and make their dreams come true.<p>

<b>Carol Bellamy<br>
Executive Director<p>
<br clear=left><br>
ICDB Logo<br><br><b><a href="index.html" target="_parent">International Children's Day of Broadcasting</a><br>
<a href="../index.html" target="_parent">UNICEF UK Home Page</a><br>
<a href="../../index.html" target="_parent">OneWorld Online Home Page</a>
</body>
</html>
