<center></center>
<br clear=left><i>The material that follows has been provided by  <a href="cba_info.htm"> Commonwealth Broadcasting Association </i></a>
<hr>

<h2 align=center>PRESS RELEASE</h2>
<h2 align=center>CBA's President resigns</h2>
17.11.95<p>

The President of the Commonwealth Broadcasting Association, Mohammed Ibrahim, Director-General of the Nigerian Television Authority, has resigned. This follows the decision of the Commonwealth Heads of Government in Auckland to suspend Nigeria from Commonwealth membership. He has been succeeded by Shashi Kant Kapoor, Director-General of All India Radio. He has assumed the Presidency until elections are held at the CBA's next General Conference, in Kuala Lumpur, from 25 - 31 August 1996.<p>









<hr>
