<b><FONT SIZE=6>Dear Head of Customer Services</font></b><br>


I am extremely concerned to hear that many people making clothes sold in the UK work very long hours in unsafe - even dangerous - factories, on rates of pay which exploit the poor. do you have a code of conduct protecting clothing workers - a set of minimum standards that guaranteed humane factory conditions? And if so, could you explain how you make sure it is always implemented?
<p>

I believe that retailers are in a position of responsibility, and have considerable influence over suppliers' work practices.
<p>

Please help secure basic rights for people working in the clothes industry.
<br>
