<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>7 : De Deo / About God</TITLE></HEAD><body>

<center><h2><hr><a name="top">The Text </a>of 'De Deo' </center></h2><h3><center>Copyright : globalprojects.org</h3></center>

1. <a href="7ephilo.htm">Return to our Philosophy Main Page.</a><br>

2. <a href="7nfilo.htm">Terug naar de Afdeling voor Filosofie.</a><br>

3. <a href="7ededeo.txt">Download 'De Deo' (17.778 bytes).</a><br>

4. <a href="welcome.htm">Return to the Welcome Page of the GHProject.</a><br><hr>

<pre>



DE DEO



Antwerp, 1995

by Wim van den Dungen



---



111



De Pace Perfecta Luce

On Perfect Peace with Light



---



0 : Divine Darkness



§ 1 (Alpha) God's essence ('pleromic' full-emptiness) is only for God to be in. 

The Divine procession starts when God begins realizing GOD & ends at the Jubilee of

Jubilees (JJ) when He celebrates His last Cosmos. Between beginning & end, God's Plan

proceeds from God, i.e. God is 'becoming' more than essence ('ousia'), He creates

existence ('energeia'). God's essence is inaccessible to Its outside ('esse subsistens'). It

is Its own first cause ('causa sui'). It is for God to partake in. God (YHadonaiVY) shows

Himself through His Cosmoi. But to what He (as Elohîm) manifests, God is potential,

silent & withdrawn, i.e. an unknowable Divine darkness.

 

§ 2  The Cosmoi are born, live, die and are reborn through a Divine Comedy (God

realizing GOD). When each & every point of God's Infinite Space finally has been a living 

Kether, making all of Space lit up (mirroring GOD through Himself as God realizing GOD)

THE GREAT JOY bursts forth. The onefold Light of this JJ shines once and forever. The 

Divine, God Creator, understood as bipolar (i.e. transcendent, unqualified, potential & 

immanent, qualified, real) is paradoxical, apophatic, onefold, perfect and unique.



§ 3  Three veils cover God. They stand between Man & God as a cloud of unknowing, 

for God is One God Alone : 

0 = Absolute No-Thing-ness or Ain ; ?

the Will of God to Realize or not to Realize GOD  ;

00 = Infinite Space or Ain Soph ;  

all possibilities receiving this Will in order to bestow :

000 = Limitless Light or Ain Soph Aur ; !

a Hidden Light shining within God's Infinite Space.



00 : Divine Procession



§ 4  Creation is 'real' because Some-Thing came out of No-Thing. This emanation is not 

God's essence, but God's Energy. It is His Life. God's essence is a 'potential' reality, His 

existence a 'manifest' reality. So this outpouring is His procession. Creation serves the 

JJ, when God -through His Fatherhood as Crowned Creator- realizes GOD. At the JJ all 

ends & only GOD is all essences & existences ; all is One totally & perfectly selfrealized 

GOD-Self.

 

§ 5  Is His existence a 'deification' of each & every point of Infinite Space ? Each 

Cosmos being but a small particle of this Space containing all options which -at the Final 

End- all have become real ? When All Ideal Is Real & All Reality Is Ideal only GOD  

remaineth.



§ 6  The procession is the outside of God. God's essence does not imply necessity. This 

begins when God stops being potential (i.e. when He exists). In order to realize GOD, 

God had to carve a hollow, constrict Its Aur & repolarize It. For He is the Great Architect 

of His Cosmoi. 



§ 7  Because the procession takes place outside God, life is a Divine Comedy ; a play of 

the Divine with the DIVINE for the sake of God's willed GOD-realization as GOD-Self. 

Behold : 

a) God's will to know Himself as GOD (vacating Space) ;

b) the contraction of the Light of this hollow to One point ;

c) the outpouring of this Kether of this present Cosmos by the Operations of His Divine 

Trinity, fashioning the holy sevenfold order of our Creator through finite but Divine 

forms.



000 : Divine Exterior



§ 8  The veils cover God's interiority. They can be rendered only by GOD. Because God 

willed GOD, God willed the separation (bridged by the Kether of each Cosmos) between 

the hidden interior & Its procession, the exterior. The finite Cosmoi are contained within 

God who, hyper-existing in Kether as Our Father, enfolds them. Blessed is He !

 

§ 9  Tradition states that Will (Absolute No-Thing) carved out a Letter in Infinite Space 

(Absolute All). God contracted the Light of that vacated hollo to One singular point of

force and made It repolarize. So was born the outpouring Crown (or Light-fountain) of 

God's exterior (the Father of this Cosmos) making God the Creator of this Creation.



§ 10 The Will of God, the Act of allowing a Contraction to happen & the Outpouring of 

the Kingdom are the Spendours given to Malkuth to behold the sevenfold Law of 

Existence.



§ 11 Kether is a dimensionless Monad, a Cosmic Father & Creator ; the immanent mode 

of the Absolute. The Seven Laws originate from His Trinity. His is a divine mode of 

alternation. The interior non-manifested Potential & Its exterior manifestation as a 

Creative & Divine Hyper-Existing Life-Energy are both separated & united.



§ 12 Kether is both the Potential & the Real. His hyper-existence is the Ever-Becoming-

God, the perpetual change permeating the illusionary permanence of the Cosmoi. Our 

Father's hyper-activity makes virtual & real to be divided for the ultimate goal of the Final 

Consumption of God -through an infinite, infinitely His, infinite realizations- by GOD (Omega). 



---



REMARKS



The core of this theology is apophatic (only silence speaks about God's essence), 

monistic (if God is not alone there is no God, for God is One and Alone), pan-energetic 

(the One Creator permeates His Cosmos always and everywhere), hierarchical (God 

creates a Creator, Who, as a Trinity, through 7 Laws creates 4 different planes of 

manifestation), theurgical (through the operations of the Order His Energy can always be 

channeled) and qabalistic (God does not exist. God does not hyper-exist, God exists in 

an ineffable, pure, infinite, potential, virtual way). THAT Essence can never be known 

(i.e. 'finitum non capax infiniti'). So apophatism subscribes to the view that God is

and remains transcendent.  



Considered to be of importance in all Western monotheistic theological systems based 

on scriptural revelation (a 'Holy Book'), i.e. Judaism (Tora), Christianism (New 

Testament) & Islam (Koran), transcendentalism implies a radical dualism between God & 

His World. So the World is a real paradox !



God can not be spoken of as 'He'. For God is both personal & impersonal and moreover 

transcends every antinomy. Is God one-fold, naked, virginal, virtual, potential, pure ? Is 

God not always somewhere, everywhere & beyond ? Concerning God unknowing reigns. 



Not unlike Brahman when asleep (nirguna), God can only be approached by negating all 

what is not God, i.e. all possible dimensions of the present Cosmos (cfr. ps-Dionusios & 

John the Scot, but see also the 'neti-neti'-method of the brahmins). God is like the 

absent King of a Kingdom which remains in perfect order (Deus absconditus). The three 

veils cover God. Can God show Himself to His World as He wills ? 



Our mystic tradition & inner teaching holds that God created each Creator of the Worlds. 

God = 0 : an unknowable unity, virtual and one-fold.

The Creator = 1 : a knowable variety under creative unity.



The latter is God manifesting (actualizing) as a particular Cosmic CreatorSelf, i.e. the 

contraction to a point of one out of many possibilities of God's Infinite Space of 

virtualities. He is and shall be. He is that what He is. He is never out of Himself, lost for 

Himself or without foreknowledge of all that comes after Him, for He is the King, the 

One Ruler of the Universe, both visible and invisible. He is the unity, the concentration, 

the pressure and the fountain of light out of which all has been generated. Blessed is He, 

for if it pleases Him,  He reveals Himself to us mortals. He is the only will to follow. The 

only law, love, way, purity, sanctity and holiness. To know Him, the Supreme Being, is 

like knowing All which is like Nothing for God. This alternation is crucial to bestow what 

was received. Christians call Him 'Abba', Father. 



Both are paradoxically divided for the ultimate goal of union. God created His Majesty, 

King of His First Universe, Prima Causæ of that First Cosmos. At the end of that Order 

light and darkness were divided. This is the first Jubilee. At one point infinity will have 

been infinitely 'filled' (the end of the series of cardinal numbers will have been reached). 

This happens at the Jubilee of the Last Cosmos, also Jubilee of Jubilees. Between two 

Cosmoi spacetime vanishes. 



At the end of the Last Cosmos all possibilities have become manifest so that Infinite 

Space reflects All Worlds and God beholds through this infinite number of CreatorSelves 

GOD. Unity and variety are one.



It is essential to distinguish God (essence unknown) from His work (or known 

existence). God written as : "YHadonaiVH" is pronounced "Adonai", the Creator 

"Elohîm". God is one-fold, singular (0), "Elohîm" is a masculine plural (1) of a feminine 

noun and means : "Gods & Goddesses".



The One Supreme Being fashioned the Cosmos together with 9 Divine Beings, both 

active (right pillar, i.e. creational) & passive (left pillar, i.e. generational).



In Genesis the 10 Sephiroth emerge as the result of 10 Divine utterances. These 

utterances indicate the nature of the work of each Sephira, all connected by 22 different 

paths, shaping the Tree of Life, i.e. the lightmatrix & the natural laws of our Cosmos. 

The first three utterances relate to the First Three of the Elohîm. They constitute the 

World of Atziluth.



1.And Elohim said : Let there be light = AHYH

2.And Elohim said : Let there be a firmament = YH

3.And Elohim said : Let there be earth = YH Elohîm



Who knows God ? Infinite space, endless light ... a small hollow constricted upon which 

I AM LIGHT is whispered ?



The nature of the First of the Elohîm is revealed as LIGHT. I am and shall be LIGHT. 

Consider All of Divinity, i.e. God (singular) and Elohîm (plural) : "YHadonaiVH Elohîm". 

Our Lord, blessed is He, is not against other gods & goddesses. He, the First of the 

Elohîm, is their Supreme Ruler from which They (the other Elohîm) receive their Light in 

order to bestow and  fashion His living Cosmos. Is He not the Lord of Abraham, Isaak, 

Mozes, Jesus Christ & Mohammed ? The Lord who reveals Himself both (objective) as 

Supreme Cause of the present Cosmos as well as in a (subjective) personal, private 

experience (in body, mind, soul & spirit) ?     



In the Old Convenant, this Father (. 1), permanently created Energy for the sake of the 

cosmic creativity of His Hierarchy of Elohîm (Y or Chockmah, 2) which fructified the 

roots & matrix or the Mother (H or Binah, 3) and caused the birth of both Son (V or 

Tiphareth, 6) & (fallen) Daughter (final H or Malkuth, 10). Behind the Plan of the Father, 

YHadonaiVH was, is and shall be recognized.



Apophatism gives form to transcendentalism by stressing the  power of unknowing, i.e. 

a special living knowledge obtained by allowing the mind to contemplate spiritual heights 

and depths while simultaneously restricting any of its attempts to move beyond its 

natural limits. 



This living knowledge (gnosis, intuition, intellectual perception) was known to the early 

qabalists as 'Daath'. It was, is & will be the foundation of all spiritual progress, i.e. the 

awakening of the experience of the omnipresence of the hyper-existence of our Father. 

Through Daath His Presence (or  'shekinah') can be experienced in consciousness. When 

a complete assimilation occurs, consciousness may learn to touch the cosmic state at 

will.



Qabalah is the only systematical spiritual calculus which takes into account : 



a) the fundamental differences between the words 'God' (i.e. "YHadonaiVH", or Lord) & 

'Creator' (i.e. "Elohîm", or Divine Beings) ; 

b) the distinction between the singularity of God and the plurality of the hierarchical 

Divine Beings (i.e. God's essence or interior versus God's Kingdom or exterior) ;

c) the distinctions between potential being, super (or hyper)-being, being & not-being.  



These distinctions are necessary in the light of God's Will to realize -through His Cosmoi- 

GOD,which happens only once & is conceived of as taking place after the End of the 

Worlds or Jubilee of the Last Cosmos (cfr. the "apokatastasis" of Origen or the "Jubilee 

of Jubilees" of the qabalists). This duality is seen in Hinduism as the dissolution at the 

end of the World (pralaya) versus the creation of a new Cosmos (manvantara). So the 

idea of a cyclic return of manifestation is clearly Eastern (compare this with Herakleitos' 

view). 



When Brahman sleeps (the impassive ground of all creation) there is no manifestation (or 

'nirguna Brahman'). When He awakens He is the Activity of the primal constituants of 

matter, the 'gunas' or ('saguna Brahman'). As such He (or 'Îshvara') simultaneously 

creates by his mâyâ the new (Vishnu) after having destroyed the old ( iva), and this till 

the end of His Day (or 'brahmic cycle'). The JJ moves beyond by suggesting the end of 

the cyclic return itself. 



In the Mândûkya Upanisad Lord Î vara is seen as the first emanation from the Absolute 

Brahman. In the sphere of the World He is absolutely supreme, but in relationship to 

Brahman He exists in so far as he is an emanation of this Absolute Brahman. The 

liberated soul (âtman), as Shankara explains in his Brahmasûtras (4.17-21) never 

identifies with Îshvara but passes clean beyond Him into the undifferentiated nirguna 

Brahman. In His capacity of Lord of Illusion, occupied with the affairs of the World, and 

as supreme object of worship He, Îshvara is alone. This privilege is His, not of any soul, 

bound or released. A 'trimûrti' occurs :



1. I am the One creator : Îshvara (= saguna Brahman)

2. I am Divine maintenance (Dharma) : Vishnu (Krisna) 

3. I am Divine dissolution :  Shiva



Although the duality between the One transcendent God and the immanent Creators of 

the cosmoi is implied by the fact of the World and the idea of becoming -both necessary 

to the birth of the Cosmoi- its polarity is harmonized by a 'tertium comparationis' : 

Kether. The dyad ensues a triad : 



God's essence, God's exterior & God-the-Creator. Abba, first of the Divine Beings, 

Godhead of the Trinity or Supernal Triad : He who is love (Father), He who is the 

beloved (Son) and He who is loving (Holy Spirit). The ever-begotten unity is called in 

christian qabalah "Father", filiation "Son" (Chockmah) and understanding "Holy Spirit" 

(Binah). 

 

Old Convenant (Mozes)=====New Convenant (Christ)



1. I AM THAT AM : light====ABBA, father

2. YH : heaven========YHshinVH, His Son Iéshoua' 

3. YH Elohîm : earth===== YHshinVH Elohîm, their Spirit



The revelations of Mohammed ibn Abdallah (570 - 632) are plain. The God (or 'Allah') 

wants a righteous planetary society and a pure religion. His devotees are immediately 

made unworldly so that they may concentrate on the Koran and the study of the signs of 

Nature, the epiphany of Allah, allowing man to glimps into His Might. Man can never 

know Allah as He is. Where Allah exists, Man is not. This is His final Law.



Allah, the One with Many Names, surely is the most perfect expression of the intuitional 

foundation of monotheism, i.e. God can not be known, felt or experienced. Distinctions 

between God and His Creator are considered to be of no real importance. 



The devotee of The One God Alone, i.e. Allah, is unable to experience the Divine 

directly. "YHadonaiVH Elohîm" (= the Divine) is absolutely different from the World 

Allah created. 



The idea that God's exterior, being part of Cosmos, can be known will be refuted on the 

grounds that hyper-existence is so paradoxical and non-verbal that a very firm theology 

of the Divine is impossible or highly exemplaric and thus too rare to allow for its 

incorporation into a planetary theosocial view on the natural bonds between Allah and 

the World.



That Allah is able to illuminate His devotees is not rejected. But for orthodox theologians 

this does not mean a transfiguration (of the human soul into Allah Himself). Allah is One. 

The idea that Chockmah & Binah are co-eternal with Kether is rejected on the grounds 

that the lightning flash decended from 1 to 2 and next to 3. Allah is both 0 and 1, i.e. 1 

= 0. So YH VH is rejected, for the Name of God can not be divided, even not by a man 

born without sin (i.e. a prophet).



Due to the experiences of Abû Yazîd, Abû Sa'îd and Junayd, a dose of Indian Vedânta 

was injected into Sûfism, the mystical body of Islam. Their efforts clearly show the 

necessity to bridge the gulf between Allah and His devotees. The Koran clearly states 

that Allah chooses for Himself a Son, but he is not co-substantial with Allah, being but 

the best creation has to offer (these Sons are the most pure of His devotees). 



The Old Convenant was physical but impersonal (shekinah) & expressed Binah. The New 

Convenant was superphysical & personal, expressing Chockmah (YH VH). Allah ignited a 

global social action (Kether). Jews have to accept Jezus as anoited. Christians have to 

differentiate (in Atziluth) between YHshinVH -Jezus- (Chockmah) and Christ (Tiphareth), 

son of Mary (Yesod), from Nazareth (Malkuth). Muslims have to accept transfiguration 

(the liberated soul becoming Divine). In doing so these mystical, relational & radical faces

of monotheism may strike a rare & fragile peaceful balance.



Types of Realities



1. potential reality : Ain Sof Aur «0»

not being & not nonbeing : - (B and - B) : 

God



--- 



2. creative reality : Kether : « 1 & 2 & 3 »

hyper-being & potential reality : Bh and  -(B and  -B) :

Creator



3. manifest reality : Cosmos : 1, ... 10 



 manifest supernal hyper-reality : 1 + 2  + 3 :

 Godhead = Bh (hyper-being)



 manifest constructed reality : 4, 5, 6 ... 10 :

 the Universe = B (being)



---



4. negative reality : Chaos : - 10, ... - 1 

nonbeing  : - B

this is the 'excreta' or 'shadow' of the Cosmoi



5.mediator reality : Daath : can not be numbered

being & nonbeing : B and  - B 

this 'knowledge' is gained though living spiritual practice</pre><hr><a href="#top">Return to the Top of this Page.</a></body></html>
