<b>Why have we created these pages?</b><br>
To make life simpler for teachers and students learning about sustainable human development - especially if you are : <br>
<ul><li>battling with the 'dev-ed' sections of the UK's <b>National Curriculum for Geography</b>
<li>doing Development Studies  
<li>14-18 years old
<li>doing GCSEs or A-levels.  
</ul>


<p><b>But these pages are not just for Geographers and Dev-Edders!</b><br>
Why not? Because the material is divided into themes - like: 
<ul><li>Population
<li>Economic development
<li>Environment
<li>Literacy
<li>Health
<li>Conflict
</ul><p>

<p>
<br>
<b>... which should also be useful to teachers and students of many other subject areas - like: </b>
<ul><li>Economics
<li>Religious Education/Moral Philosophy
<li>Sociology
<li>English 
<li>Environmental Studies
</ul>


<b>How do the pages work?</b><br>
It's very simple. You can either: 
<ul>
<li>go to our <a href="index.html#sch">list of subject areas</a>
<li>use our <a href="../owo_options.html">search index for a specific topic</a>

