<center><h1>Receiving Information</h1></center>





<h2>Europe</h2>
<b>Times:</b> 24 hours (CET=GMT + 2 hours)<br>
<b>Distribution:</b> Cable, direct-to-home<br>
<b>Reception: </b>Satellite: Eutelsat II F1 13 degrees E Superbeam; downlink frequency: 1169.66 Mhz. Free-to-air<p>


<h2>Asia/ Middle East</h2>
<b>Times: </b>24 hours (Middle East=GMT + 3 hours)<br>
<b>Distribution:</b> Cable, direct-to-home, terrestrial rebroadcast.<br>
<b>Reception:</b> Satellite: Asia Sat 1, 105.5 degrees E Southern beam; downlink frequency: 3940 Mhz south<br>
<b>Equipment: </b>Satellite receiving dish size varies, so consult dealer.<br>
<b>Contact:</b> For South Asia and Middle East: STAR TV, 12/F Hutchison House, 10 Harcourt Rd, Central, Hong Kong. Tel: +852 2532 1777. Free-to-air<p>


<h2>Japan</h2>
<b>Times: </b>24 hours, including four hours a day with Japanese audio between 2000-2400 Japanese Standard Time. (JST = GMT + 9 hours)<br>
<b>Distribution:</b> Cable, direct-to-home, terrestrial rebroadcast.<br>
<b>Reception:</b> Satellite: JCSAT-2; 154 degrees E Japan Beam; downlink frequency: 12673.25 Mhz.<br>
<b>Equipment:</b> available on cable.<br>
<b>Contact:</b> Satellite News Corporation, JBP Oval Bldg, 52-2, Jingu-mae 5-chome, Shibuya-ku, Tokyo 150, Japan. Tel: +81 3 3406 9777. Annual subscription fee.<p>


<h2>Africa</h2>
<b>Times: </b>Sat 0700-0800; Sun 1700-11900: Mon-Fri 0300-1100, 1400-1600, 2000-2100 Central African Time (CAT = GMT + 2hours)<br>
<b>Distribution:</b> Cable, direct-to-home.<br>
<b>Reception:</b> Satellite: Intelsat VI 27.5 degrees W. east Hemi beam; downlink freq: 3.650 Ghz.<br>
<b>Equipment:</b> M-NET Delta 9000+ decoder; satellite receiver dish; 3.5-3.8m.<br>
<b>Contact:</b> M-NET, PO Box 4950, Randburg, 2125, Republic of South Africa. Tel: +27 11 889 1106. Annual subscription fee.<p>


<h2>New Zealand</h2>
Terrestrial rebroadcast daily on Horizon Pacific stations for Auckland, the Waikato, Wellington and Dunedin, overnight on TV1.

<h2>Canada</h2>
Cable rebroadcast daily, CBC Newsworld.<p>

