<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>HYDROLOGICAL STRUCTURES DETECTION</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY  BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">
    <!-- Changed by: , 16-Feb-1996 -->
      <h2> OCEAN </h2>

      <h3><a href="/French/Etudes/Teledetection/ocean.html"> <img align=middle src="/gifs/FLAGFR.jpg" alt="french flag">Cliquez ici pour lire la version francaise</A></h3>
      <img src="/gifs/bar_marbre_noir2.gif"><br><br>
      <BIG>

	<strong>Study</strong>:
      <P>
	Identification of mesoscale hydrological structures which can be detected by a satellite observing the sea surface.
      <P>	
	Detection of oceanic structures using AVHRR data 9temperature) and CZCS (chlorophyl). The studie concern the Gulf of Biscay (France). For AVHRR data, an archieve covering the years 1978 to 1985 has been used.
      <P>
	CZCS images provided in the framework of the Ocean Colour European Archive Network (OCEAN) have been used.
      <P>
	An operational system data processing has been developped. It permits the radiometric and geometric registration of the images (AVHRR and CZCS), the clouds detection, the structure identification and their archive.
      <P>	
	The final purpose of this studie concerns the realisation of a system for detection and prediction of the variation of the structures.
      <P>
	<strong>Client </strong>: French Navy, EPSHOM ( Etablissement principal du service hydrographique et oceanographique de la marine )

      <P>
	<strong>Participants</strong> : ACRI, GM-Image, Ecole des Mines de Paris.
      <P> 

      </BIG>

      <hr>
      <P>
	AVHRR Data, July 8, 1979 17H00
	<IMG SRC="gif/avhrr.gif" ALT= "AVHRR">
      <P>
      <hr>
      <p>
	CZCS data, July 8, 1979, 15H00
	<IMG SRC="gif/czcs.gif" ALT= "AVHRR">
	<BR>
      <hr>
      <p>
