  <HEAD>
    <TITLE> ANSWER </TITLE>
    <!-- Created by: Gilbert BARROT, 25-Jan-1996 -->
    <!-- Changed by: Gilbert BARROT, 25-Jan-1996 -->
    <!-- Changed by: , 18-Nov-1996 -->
  </HEAD>

  <BODY  BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

      <CENTER>
      <H1> 
	ANSWER<P>
	Software tool for the resolution of Navier-Stokes, energy and mass transport equations in turbulent reacting flows<P>
      </H1>
      </CENTER>

      <HR>

      <FONT SIZE="+2">
	A demonstration is available <A HREF="/English/Products/download.html">here</A>.
      </FONT>


      <CENTER>
	<IMG ALIGN=TOP ALT="ANSWER Main example" SRC="gifs/answer.gif"><P>
      </CENTER>

      <HR>

      <BIG>
	ANSWER is a comprehensive mathematical model for simulation of laminar or turbulent fluid flow, heat and mass transfer, with or without swirl, chemical reactions and combustion. Arbitrary 2D or 3D geometry, with or without internal obstacles are accommodated. Single or multiple inlets, outlets, sources and free surface may be present. <P>

	It is a highly modular program which is suitable for a wide range of practical fluid flow problems in petrochemical, chemical, aerospace, mechanical and civil engineering applications. Typical petrochemical applications include flows in pipes, reactors, combustors and process chambers.<P>

	The user interface is through the conversational FREEFORM language which provides for simple English-like command syntax. The result can be graphically displayed by the acrPLOT, post-processor, which can generate charts for flow vectors, contours, grids, 3D surface plots and X-Y plots at any cross section.<P>

      <P>
      </big>

	<BIG> Keywords :
      <UL>
	<LI> Momentum transport
	<LI> Heat transfer
	<LI> Mass transfer
	<LI> Turbulence
	<LI> Combustion
	<LI> Radiation
	<LI> Droplet transport
	<LI> Soot & particulates
      </UL>
    </big>

      <HR>

      <CENTER>
	<big> 
	  Some examples<P>
      </big>
      </CENTER>

      <DL>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="blade.html"><BIG>Bladed rotating disk</big></A>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="car.html"><BIG>Automobile aerodynamics</big></A>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="clutch.html"><BIG>Oil flow in a clutch</big></A>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="gifs/answer.dat"><BIG>Dataset example</big></A>
      </DL>

      <!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
