<HEAD>
<TITLE>Simulateur d'Instrument d'Observation de la Terre</TITLE>
<!-- Created by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 29-Jan-1996 -->
<!-- Changed by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 29-Jan-1996 -->


</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

<H1>Simulateur d'Instrument d'Oservation de la Terre</H1>
<BIG>
<B>ACRI</B> has developed several Earth Observation System
Simulators. These software are used during all phases of space and
ground segment design, implementation and exploitation for an Earth
observation mission. They allow characterisation and quantification of
the detailed specifications, and validation of the different modules
of the system.

<P>

The simulation software describes the different modules or components
of a space system from the signal emission to the ground receiving and
processing facility including the sensor and data acquisition on board
the space platforms.


<P>

The application is Earth Observation from space but also applicable to
airbone systems and ground based or underwater systems to monitor
environment.

<P>
The actual simulators are : 
<DL>
<DT><DD><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rectangle_vert.gif">
<A HREF="../../Studies/Spatial/GOSS.html">GOSS Simulator</A>

<DT><DD><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rectangle_vert.gif">
<A HREF="../../Studies/Spatial/MERSS.html">MERSS Simulator</A>

<DT><DD><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rectangle_vert.gif">
<A HREF="../../Studies/Spatial/SEAWSS.html">SeaWifs Simulator</A>
</DL>
</BIG>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<P>
<IMG align=top src="/gifs/bar_marbre_noir2.gif">

