<HEAD>
<TITLE>WEFAXSAT</TITLE>
<!-- Created by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 29-Jan-1996 -->
<!-- Changed by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 29-Jan-1996 -->


</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

<H1>WEFAXSAT</H1>

<H1>Satellite Images Acquisition System</H1>
<h3><A HREF="/French/Produits/WEFAX/wefax.html"><img alt=french flag align=middle src="/gifs/FLAGFR.jpg"> Cliquez ici pour lire la version francaise</h3></A>
<img src="/gifs/bar_marbre_noir2.gif"> <BR><BR>

<CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=TOP SRC="total_terre.gif" ALT="Terre">
</CENTER>

<H2>Why a satellite data acquisition System ?</H2>

<BIG>

METEOSAT, NOAA, etc... are extremely satisfying satellites as far as following up the European and African continents and the ocans are concerned.
<P>


Knowing the weather and the climate (cloud movement, weather forecast, rain index, rising forecast, sea surface temperature, cloud analysis...), accessing good quality images, especially those from METEOSAT, represent a tremendous tool for a great number of laboratories and industries, as well as for agriculture. 

<P>

A large identified users community has expressed the need for information 
tools operating on environment. Applications are numerous, for example :

<UL>
<LI> Coastal protection
<LI> Climate and meteorology
<LI> Observation, security
<LI> Tourism and leisure
<LI> Fishing and aquaculture
<LI> Sea traffic
<LI> Agriculture and stock breeding
</UL>		

<P>

Earth observation datas are directly usable, in real time, by the <b>WEFAXSAT</b> system.	

<H2>FONCTIONNALITIES </H2>

All datas go through several stages so as to be usable. 

<b>WEFAXSAT</b> : the acquisition and processing system developed and commercialised by GM-IMAGES, changes a computer into a satellite reception station.
<P>


The system includes a 1 meter diameter dish, an analogic reception station a digitisation and image processing board and of course,  WEFAXSAT software.

<P>


This reception set allows the picking-up of WEFAX format METEOSAT, GOES, 
GMS type geostationary satellites as well as APT format for polar satellites 
like NOAA and METEOR. 


<H2> WEFAXSAT SOFTWARE PACKAGE </H2>


WEFAXSAT software package offers advanced WEFAX image processing 
functions together with a WEFAX reception station providing meteorological 
satellite digital images, which are received, stored, processed or even 
animated.
<p>
You can see below two METEOSAT animations.
<br> ( You need a mpeg viewer on your system to run animations )
<ul>
<li> <a href="/mpeg/meteo.mpg"> METEOSAT 1</a> (150K)
<li> <a href="/mpeg/meteo2.mpg"> METEOSAT 2</a> (70K)
</ul>

<p>
<b>WEFAWSAT system description </b>

<UL>

<LI> Pull down menu type user interface, entirely manageable with the mouse

<LI> Geographical zone and spectral band of acquisition controlled by the user. Self-automatic controlled entirely, with a possibility of manual control


<LI> Dissemination hours of METEOSAT  channels 1 and 2 recorded in a text file form (interactive updating)

<LI>  Last 75 images may be stored on the hard disk, that is to say 15 for each of the following zones : COX (CO2 et CO3), CXD (de C1D ˆ C9D), DX (de D1 ˆ D9), TOTAL (CTOT, DTOT) and WEFAX

<LI> Management and maintenance of the recorded images and a possibility of compacting them through various methods

<LI> Possibility of acquiring without storing, and of displaying continuously the images

<LI> Interactive creation of color (or shads of grey) animation loops with image choice, speed variator.

<LI> 256 color display with graphic resolution choice (480x640, 600 x800 and 768x1024)

<LI> 3 levels of zoom directly accessible through mouse interaction 

<LI> Interactive contrast arrangement controlled by the user

<LI> Oscilloscope function allowing a detailed analysis of the signal on a recorded image

<LI> Color output on various types of printers

<LI> Possible interface  with other types of image formats such as TITUS, ARTIST, PCX, BMP.

</UL>


<H2>WEFAXSAT SYSTEM CONFIGURATION </H2>

In  order to use WEFAXSAT system you should have an IBM-PC compatible 
with 4 Mo mem. computer.
<P>

WEFAXSAT also accepts a Microsoft - or compatible - mouse. GM-IMAGES 
declines any responsability as to the use of non compatible hardware with 
WEFAXSAT software.

<P>


The various WEFAXSAT modules will operate more or less quickly 
depending on the processor and on the access specifications of the hard 
disk.

<BR><BR>
