<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>CEO Presentation</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 30-Jan-1996 -->


</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

<IMG ALIGN=TOP SRC="/gifs/ceolineup.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/backceo.gif" ALT="Coastal page"></A>
<A HREF="cz_help.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/help.gif"></A>
<BR>
<IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/ceolinedown.gif"><BR>


<B>EUROPEAN EARTH OBSERVATION SYSTEM</B>
<P>

<B>CENTRE FOR EARTH OBSERVATION</B>
<P>

<P>
<big>
Description of the CEO Concept<P>
<P>

Pathfinder Study on Coastal Zone
<P>
<HR>
<P>

The European Commission and the European Space Agency (ESA), together with
member states, have decided to unite their expertise in order to set up a
project for the observation of the Earth called EEOS (European Earth
Observation System). This project, started in November 1992, consists
essentially of :
<P>
<DL>
<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif"> The identification of the multiple sources of earth observation data in
Europe ;

<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif"> The assessment of the requirements of users of earth observation products and services ;

<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif"> The promotion of these sources of information and services ;

<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif"> The improvement of access and exchange.

</DL>
<P>

More precisely, the programme's missions are related to <B>earth observation
data, products and services</B> as follows :
<P>

To promote their knowledge and distribution from different origins (on-site
measurements, remote sensing, models, ...) ;
<P>

To facilitate their use and to ensure their accessibility and availability
;
<P>

To provide a European interface with other international systems of Earth
Observation such as the American system EOSDIS (Earth Observation System Data
and Information System) and the Japanese EOIS (Earth Observation Information
System).
<P>
<P>

The European Union's contribution to this project consists in the setting up of
a structure called CEO (Centre for Earth Observation) which will ensure an
interface between the users and the data, the subsequent products and
associated services.
<P>

<P>

<IMG ALIGN=TOP ALT=" " SRC="gifs/youdale1.gif">

<P>
<P>

The principal objective of the CEO is to provide services oriented towards (and
by) the user. This action should be in conjunction with the existing
infrastructures (such as networks) and existing initiatives (such as other
programmes) so as to promote the observation of the Earth in Europe.
<P>

The CEO's success will depend on the association of four key elements :
potential users, the provision of services, an electronic network and an
exchange service called EWSE (European Wide Service Exchange).
<P>
<P>

In order to obtain these objectives the CEO's principal actions will be :
<DL>
<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
To encourage a better communication between the users ;

<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
To stimulate the creation of high level products ;

<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
To contribute to a better standardisation of data and related products
so as to promote and ensure quality ;

<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
To promote the concept and utilisation of decentralised archives,
data banks and associated services for the observation of the earth
whatever their origins ;

<DT><DD>  <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
To improve the visibility of Earth observation services and expertise.

</DL><P>

The essential idea is that the CEO will in time be managed by people concerned
by Earth observation activities. The Commission will encourage the setting up
and the operation of the system (until the end of 1998).
<P>
<P>

At the moment the CEO is a concept and it is necessary that people concerned by
Earth observation make their wishes and suggestions known in order to define
and make optimal use of this system.
<P>
<P>

The project of the CEO consists of four phases. The first made possible the
actual concept of the CEO. We are, at the moment, in the second phase
(pathfinder study) whose principal objective is to identify what exists at
present for finding out the needs of the users. Its goal is to produce enough
information to enable the next phase to be undertaken, that is to say the
conception of the final system and its take-off (until 1998). The operational
phase will start in 1999 and will be run by the users of the system.
<P>
<P>

In order to limit the size of this work of identification, the Commission
thought it preferable to address user requirements in two ways :
<P>

<DL>
<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
to look at a sample of application areas in some detail (i.e. marine
altimetry, agriculture and forestry, global change, urban development and
lastly coastal zones)
<DD>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
to look at an overview of the requirements of Institutes in Europe. This was
divided into four geographical groups based on the status and scope of existing
industry and programmes as follows :
<DD>

<DL>
<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">group 1 :

<DD> Germany, France, Italy
and United Kingdom ;
<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">group 2 :
<DD> Belgium, Denmark, Luxembourg and The
Netherlands ;
<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">group 3 :
<DD> Spain, Greece, Ireland and Portugal ;
<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">group 4 :
<DD> Austria, Finland, Iceland, Norway and Sweden.

</DL>
</DL>
<P>

The international network Eurocoast, the
<A HREF="contacts/MEDIAS.html">MEDIAS-FRANCE</A> corporation,
<A HREF="contacts/GKSS.html">GKSS</A> (Germany),
and <A HREF="contacts/MARNET.html">MARNET</A> (Greece)
represent the consortium led by
<A HREF="contacts/ACRI.html">ACRI</A> (France)
which has been selected by the European Commission for the part related to the
identification of users requirements in the coastal zone.
<P>
<P>

In order to do this we are, at the moment, having an information campaign and
conducting enquiries of users and suppliers. These enquiries are carried out by
direct discussions with those involved with coastal zones, and by the sending
out of a questionnaire to a representative sample of the community.
<P>
<P>

The choice of this representative sample is bound to be limited, and it is
possible that certain organisations who would like to have said something about
this subject have not been consulted. If you know anybody in this case or if
you need further information concerning the CEO : do not please hesitate to
contact us (you will find the list of person to contact at the beginning of the
questionnaire).
<P>
<P>

We hope that the attached questionnaire will give to numerous users the
opportunity to clearly expose their needs and wishes in order to contribute
directly with a maximum of efficiency to the planned coastal zone part of the
CEO and to make it as adapted to the requirements of the community as
possible.
<P>
<P>

We are aware that our community is often solicited by questionnaires and
enquiries, and we are most grateful for the reception you would be prepared to
give to this one.
<P>
<P>
</big>

<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">

