<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Relevant Servers</TITLE>
    <!-- Created by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 10-Jan-1995 -->
    <!-- Changed by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 30-Jan-1996 -->


  </HEAD>
  <BODY BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

    <IMG ALIGN=TOP SRC="/gifs/ceolineup.gif"><BR>
    <A HREF="index.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/backceo.gif"></A>
    <A HREF="cz_help.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/help.gif"></A><BR>

    <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/ceolinedown.gif"><BR>


    <H1>Relevant Servers</H1>
    <big>
      This page tries to summarize the actual list of servers concerning
      Coastal Zone information.
    <P>

      Feel free to contact us at <A HREF="mailto:www@acri.fr">www@acri.fr</A> to complete this list.
    <P>

    <HR>
    <H2> Members to this project </H2>
    <DL>
    <DL>

      <DT> <A HREF="http://ceo-www.jrc.it:80/"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="gifs/ceo-logo.gif" ALT="Ceo Logo"> CEO Server (EU)</A>
    <P>
      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif"><A HREF="http://estunx.santateresa.enea.it/MERC/MERC.html"> ENEA</A>
    <P>
      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="gifs/gkss-logo.gif" ALT="WATiS Logo">
	<A HREF="http://www.gkss.de/">GKSS</A>
	with access to <A HREF="watis/CEOWATiS.html">WATiS
	  database</A>

      </DL>
      </DL>

    <HR>

    <H2>Others Servers in Europe (EU)</H2>
    <DL>
    <DL>

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.awi-bremerhaven.de/">
	  The Alfred Wegner Institute (Germany)</A>
      <DD> National research centre for Polar and marine research

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://almeria.cedex.es/">
	  CEDEX (Centro de Estudios y Experimentacion de Obras Publicas) (Spain)</A>
      <DD> Centre specialised with harbour engineering and more generally with 
	coastal engineering.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.puertos.es/">
	  Clima Maritimo: Ministery of Public Works (Spain)</A>
      <DD>This centre handles two main activities: development of a data base about Oceanography
	and development of numerical model concerning Oceanography.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://dutlru8.lr.tudelft.nl/">
	  Delft University of Technology (Netherlands)</A>
      <DD> Working towards a global atlas of maps of the mean sea surface elevation.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.esrin.esa.it/">
	  ESRIN server (ESA)</A>
      <DD>Distribute and maintaine archieved data about spatial domain.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.ifremer.fr/sismer/sommaire.htm">
	  Ifremer, WWW server</A>
      <DD> SISMER: Scientific system of information for Oceanographic domain.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.nwo.ac.uk/iosdl/">
	  IOSDL, Institute of Oceanographic Sciences Deacon Laboratory (U.K.)</A>
      <DD> The mission of this Institute is to advance understanding of the Oceanic environment.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://gds.esrin.esa.it/">GDS ESA</A>
      <DD> GDS describes Earth observation data, systems and applications.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://me-www.jrc.it/">
	  JRC, Institute for Remote Sensing Applications/Marine Environment Unit</A>
      <DD> The scope of the Marine Environment Unit is to develop, demonstrate and validate methodologies for the use of data from space and airborne Platforms in both operational applications and scientific investigations related to the marine environment.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.wcmc.org.uk/">
	  World Conservation Monitoring Centre (U.K.)</A>
      <DD> Information on Marine and Coastal Ecosystems

    </DL>
  </DL>

    <HR>
    <H2>Others Servers in others countries</H2>

    <DL>
    <DL>

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://inlet.geol.scarolina.edu/">
	  Baruch Institute for Marine Biology and Coastal Research (South Carolina U.S.A.)</A>
      <DD> Research into the ecological and commercial values of the ocean and coastal zone

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.ccpo.odu.edu/">
	  Center for Coastal Physical Oceanography (U.S.A.)</A>
      <DD>
	This center reflects the Commonwealth's commitment to exploring the interrelated effects of short term human impact and long term global change on the coastal ocean environment.   
      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www-ccs.ucsd.edu/">
	  Center for Coastal Studies, UCSD (San Diego U.S.A.)</A>
      <DD> Research unit of the Scrips Institution of Oceanography (SIO),
	For studies of coastal environment, engages the development of data acquisition
	systems and research instrumentation, and advising on coastal
	protection and sediment management.


      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://kaos.erin.gov.au/">
	  ERIN Institute (Australia)</A>
      <DD> Server about Marine and Coastal Conservation

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://fermi.jhualp.edu:80/sirc/sirc.html">
	  Johns Hopkins University Applied Physics Laboratory</A>
      <DD> Provides Real-time measurements of ocean wave vectors
	in the Southern Ocean (SIR-C/X-SAR instrument)

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://eos.nasa.gov/">
	  NASA, Earth Observation System (EOS) Information Server (U.S.A.)</A>
      <DD> Provide convenient access to program information about EOS program

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www-mipl.jpl.nasa.gov/">
	  NASA, JPL, Jet propulsion Laboratory: Physical Oceanography Distributed Active Archive Center</A>
      <DD> Archives and distributes data on ocean circulation and air-sea interactions.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://hpcc1.hpcc.noaa.gov/cop/cop-home.html">
	  NOAA, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (U.S.A.),
	  Center for Coastal Ecosystem Health, </A>
      <DD> Programs to maintain biodiversity and long-term productivity of coastal ecosystems.
	In particulary, provide information about Estuarine habitat and coastal change.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://iabp.apl.was[hington.edu">NSIDC National Snow and Ice Data Center (U.S.A.)</A>

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://info.er.usgs.gov">USGS, U.S. Geological survey</A>
      <DD> Provides information about coastal Ocean Modeling
	and in particulary about sediment transport.

      <DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/rec_rouge.gif">
	<A HREF="http://www.whoi.edu/">Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution (U.S.A)</A>
      <DD> The largest independant marine science research facility in the U.S.,
	in particulary see coastal briefs.
    </DL>
  </DL>

  </big>
