<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Help Page</TITLE>
<!-- Created by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 22-Feb-1995 -->
<!-- Changed by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 30-Jan-1996 -->


</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">



<H1>Help Page</H1>

This page gives you the most important information of the way to
use the server. It comports mainly 3 parts:

<DL>
<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
an introduction to <A HREF="#INTROWEB">WWW concept</A> and definition.

<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
the <A HREF="#ORGSERVER">general organisation</A> of this server
and how to use it.

<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
the various <A HREF="#SEARCHTOOLS">Internet Search Tools</A> to make
some requests about all you want and dream about.

<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
a brief functional <A HREF="#ICONS">description of the icons</A>
used inside the server to facilitate the browsing.
</DL>

<IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/note.gif">
<I>If you want to have a print version of this page, just choose on your
client the print facility and choose Postscript output to have a near
wysiwyg output.
</I>

<HR>
<H2><A NAME="INTROWEB">Introduction to WWW</H2>

Introducing the WWW in few lines is too difficult. So, as in the rest of
the server, we will just make a brief description and then give links to
various documents and servers describing perfectly this notion.
<P>
The main characteristic is the possibility to inter-connect thousands of
servers with different protocols like <I>ftp</I>, <I>gopher</I> or
<I>wais</I>. The other
important characteristic is the hypertext notion. Every element of the
display could be a link to an other document elsewhere in the world.
<P>
This kind of architecture gives lot of flexibility and allows to obtain
information for lots of domains. Meanwhile, this same thing makes sometimes
the search difficult to find a particular information on the network and
on the multiplicity of servers available thru Internet.

<DL>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://info.cern.ch/hypertext/WWW/TheProject.html">
the WWW project
</A>
<DD> The CERN (origin of the WWW project) Page contain all the information
about the Web project.

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://cuiwww.unige.ch/W3catalog/nsp.html">
Starting Points for Internet Exploration</A>
<DD> University of Genova builds this page to facilitate the first
steps in the WWW world. Lots of useful informations.

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/help-about.html">
Mosaic Information</A>
<DD> Gives information about Mosaic Client on X, Apple and MS Windows systems.

</DL>


<HR>
<H2><A NAME="ORGSERVER">General Organisation of the server</H2>

This server goal is to capture user requirements in the field of Coastal Zone.
To achieve this, it gives access to several pages:

<DL>
<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
A description of the Coastal Zone User Requirements Study and a CEO background.
<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
Sample Data sets
<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
User Requirements Questionnaire
<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
User Feedback Questionnaire
<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
A list of contact points (i.e. the list of the consortium list)
<DT> <DD> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
A list of interesting and related servers around the world.

</DL>

It gives also access to an help page, statistics about the server, the news and the future
plans for it.
 <P>

<HR>

<H2><A NAME="SEARCHTOOLS">Internet Search Tools</H2>

This section gives you access to the most know search tools actually
available on the net. They are very interesting to make search on a
given topic. My favourites are <STRONG>Lycos</STRONG> and
<STRONG>Internet Search</STRONG>. But all of them are really powerful.
<DL>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://home.mcom.com/home/internet-search.html">An index of index: Internet Search</A>
<DD> This server allows to make search on several ways but also have
a list of many of the others Internet Search services.

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://lycos.cs.cmu.edu/">Lycos</A>: Hunting WWW Information
<DD> Carnie Mellon University (USA) allow you to search items on
document titles and content.<BR>
<IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/note.gif">
<I>This page is a front-end for several search machines. This is very
useful because lots of connections occurs at the same time. On choising
a server, if there are too many people logged on to it,
a new server will be proposed to you.
After that, just enter the searched keyword(s) and then hit Return.
<STRONG>The results will be the same on the differents servers.
This is only different computers with the same database.</STRONG></I>


<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://webcrawler.cs.washington.edu/WebCrawler/WebQuery.html">
Web Crawler</A>
<DD> University of Washington search engine which searches on
titles and contents.


<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.cs.colorado.edu/home/mcbryan/WWWW.html">
WWWW World Wide Web Worm</A>
<DD> WWWW pores over the information in the Web and builds an index
of titles and locations.

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.town.hall.org/brokers/www-home-pages/query.html/">
WWW home pages Broker</A>
<DD> The Harvest Information Discovery and Access System (USA)


<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://cuiwww.unige.ch/w3catalog">
Centre Universitaire d'Information WWW catalog</A>
<DD> University of Geneva (Switzerland) also know as CUI W3 catalog


<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.stir.ac.uk/jsbin/js">The JumpStation Search Page</A>
<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.stir.ac.uk/jsbin/jsii">JumpStation II</A>
<DD> These will search document titles and headings.
Jump Station II allows you to search keywords.

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.rns.com/cgi-bin/nomad">Zorbamatic</A>
<DD> System that searches through document titles.


<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif">
<A HREF="http://web.nexor.co.uk/aliweb/doc/aliweb.html">ALIWEB</A>
<DD> Archie like indexing for the WEB maintaned by Nexor.
Their database is a collection of document summaries written by
their publishers and regularly updated by ALIWEB
</DL>


<HR>
<H2><A NAME="ICONS">Icons description</H2>

<DL>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/help.gif" ALT="Help">
<DD> This icon always gives you this current page. So, by clicking on this
icon (on top or bottom of a page) will always make appear this Help.
<P>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/backceo.gif" ALT="Back">
<DD> This icon is always a link to <STRONG>main page</STRONG>.
So even at the most deeper
page of the server, this will reset you at the main choice page.
<P>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/parent.gif" ALT="Up">
<DD> This icon allows you to go to main page of the actual section.
<P>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/warning.gif">
<DD> This icon denotes a warning issue for the user
(could be a non yet implemented feature or
an important directive for the user).
<P>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/note.gif">
<DD> This icon is present to give hints or precious
information on the server use.
<P>

</DL>


