<HEAD>
<TITLE>HCM Objectives</TITLE>
<!-- Created by: Jean-Michel Augusto,  6-Jan-1995 -->
<!-- Changed by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 26-Jan-1996 -->


</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">
<H1>HCM Objectives</H1>
<img src="/gifs/bar_marbre_noir2.gif">
<BR>
<BIG>
The proposed scientific and technical network aims to integrate the scientific
activities of the different participating institutes in the field of remote 
sensing, oceanography and numerical modelling. The proposed activities 
are built upon the expertise and competence already available within the 
institutes and should contribute to the following generic aims :
<UL>
<LI>
develop ant to expend where possible, algorithms that relate variable 
available from remote sensing, ocean platforms and other observations 
to processes occurring in the water column as for example heat flux, primary 
productivity and trace gas fluxes.
<LI>
to generate, archive and analyse multiannual time series of remote sensing,
 in-situ and meteorological data for a basic evaluation of time scales, 
variability and trends. 
<LI>
to select and develop models of the upper layer of the ocean to assimilate 
remote sensing and other data for process studies and for future contributions
to global models.
</UL>
More specifically, the proposed scientific network has been created on the 
existing expertise and ongoing activities of the involved institutes.
This includes the following main topics :remote sensing,experimental studies,
modelling.
<P>
<P>
<U>Results and achievements :</U> 
<P>
<b>Key words :</b>
<ul>
<li> Satellite remote sensing
<li> in-situ measurements 
<li> ocean process modelling
<li> ocean colour 
<li> primary productivity
</ul>
</BIG>

<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
